{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775887336912,"sessionID":"ses_284e24014ffe4WImNheu6RKOHU","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2245cd001JPBZBsuhAG5HpY","messageID":"msg_d7b223b4b0019vIXnz7Lbyjbzm","sessionID":"ses_284e24014ffe4WImNheu6RKOHU","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775887569023,"sessionID":"ses_284e24014ffe4WImNheu6RKOHU","part":{"id":"prt_d7b225fa3001cd4xlh5A7fIR7v","messageID":"msg_d7b223b4b0019vIXnz7Lbyjbzm","sessionID":"ses_284e24014ffe4WImNheu6RKOHU","type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me write the design.md:","time":{"start":1775887569022,"end":1775887569022}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887569034,"sessionID":"ses_284e24014ffe4WImNheu6RKOHU","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2260d5001NAr9mIHkTF43UK","messageID":"msg_d7b223b4b0019vIXnz7Lbyjbzm","sessionID":"ses_284e24014ffe4WImNheu6RKOHU","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_ade4198520894a8aa9020058","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-038: WorkloadManager Go 单元测试 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers comprehensive Go unit tests for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module of AgentCube. The workloadmanager package is the control plane API server responsible for sandbox lifecycle management (create, delete, reconcile) for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter workloads.\n\n### 1.2 Scope\n\n| Sub-package | Files | Status |\n|-------------|-------|--------|\n| `handler/sandbox_create.go` | 693 lines | **No tests** — primary gap |\n| `handler/sandbox_delete.go` | 216 lines | Covered (387 lines of tests) |\n| `handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go` | 679 lines | Covered (696 lines of tests) |\n| `handler/models.go` | 71 lines | Partially covered via delete tests |\n| `handler/constants.go` | 69 lines | Indirectly covered |\n| `reconciler/reconciler.go` | 227 lines | **No tests** — primary gap |\n| `reconciler/sync.go` | 125 lines | **No tests** — primary gap |\n| `reconciler/agentruntime.go` | 127 lines | **No tests** — primary gap |\n| `reconciler/codeinterpreter.go` | 104 lines | **No tests** — primary gap |\n| `reconciler/pod.go` | 100 lines | **No tests** — primary gap |\n| `reconciler/event_handlers.go` | 165 lines | **No tests** — primary gap |\n| `reconciler/metrics.go` | 141 lines | Covered (83 lines of tests) |\n| `reconciler/types.go` | 59 lines | Constants — indirectly covered |\n| `response/response.go` | 45 lines | Covered (110 lines of tests) |\n\n### 1.3 System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    WorkloadManager API Server                        │\n│  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                      Gin HTTP Router                          │  │\n│  └───────┬───────────────────────┬───────────────────┬───────────┘  │\n│          │                       │                   │              │\n│  ┌───────▼───────┐   ┌──────────▼──────────┐  ┌─────▼──────────┐  │\n│  │ SandboxCreate │   │  SandboxDelete      │  │ LifecycleMgr   │  │\n│  │   Handler     │   │     Handler         │  │ (GC/TTL/Idle)  │  │\n│  └───────┬───────┘   └──────────┬──────────┘  └────────────────┘  │\n│          │                       │                                  │\n│  ┌───────▼───────────────────────▼──────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                   SandboxReconciler                          │  │\n│  │  ┌──────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌──────┐  ┌───────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │AgentRT   │  │CodeInterp  │  │ Pod  │  │ Event Handlers│  │  │\n│  │  │reconcile │  │ reconcile  │  │recon │  │ (Add/Upd/Del) │  │  │\n│  │  └──────────┘  └────────────┘  └──────┘  └───────────────┘  │  │\n│  └────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                           │                                        │\n│  ┌────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                    Store Interface                            │  │\n│  │  (handler.Store / reconciler.Store — different signatures)   │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n         │                                              │\n         ▼                                              ▼\n┌──────────────────┐                        ┌──────────────────────┐\n│  K8s API Server  │                        │  Redis/Valkey Store  │\n│  (dynamic client │                        │  (session metadata)  │\n│   + informers)   │                        └──────────────────────┘\n└──────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.4 Design Principles\n\n- **Interface-based mocking**: All external dependencies are already interface-based; tests use inline mock structs.\n- **Table-driven tests**: Boundary conditions and error paths use table-driven test patterns consistent with existing tests.\n- **No external K8s cluster**: All K8s interactions use fake clients, mock listers, and mock informers.\n- **Nil-safety verification**: All public methods tested with nil receiver to ensure no panics.\n- **Metrics verification**: Prometheus metric registration verified via `reg.Gather()`.\n\n### 1.5 Package Structure (test files)\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── handler/\n│   ├── sandbox_create_test.go          # NEW — create handler tests\n│   ├── sandbox_create_helpers_test.go  # NEW — CR builder, entry points, util tests\n│   ├── sandbox_delete_test.go          # EXISTING\n│   ├── sandbox_lifecycle_test.go       # EXISTING\n│   └── models_test.go                  # NEW — request validation, data structure tests\n├── reconciler/\n│   ├── reconciler_test.go              # NEW — constructor, Run, WatchSandboxOnce\n│   ├── sync_test.go                    # NEW — syncHandler, processNextWorkItem\n│   ├── agentruntime_test.go            # NEW — reconcileAgentRuntime, mapConditionToStatus\n│   ├── codeinterpreter_test.go         # NEW — reconcileCodeInterpreter\n│   ├── pod_test.go                     # NEW — reconcilePod, buildEntryPointsFromSandboxInfo\n│   ├── event_handlers_test.go          # NEW — onAgentRuntimeAdd/Update/Delete, etc.\n│   ├── metrics_test.go                 # EXISTING\n│   └── fixtures_test.go                # NEW — shared mock types and test helpers\n├── response/\n│   └── response_test.go                # EXISTING\n└── const.go\n```\n\n### 1.6 Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Test Use |\n|------------|---------|----------|\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | v1.11.1 | assert, require |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake` | v0.34.1 | Fake dynamic client |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake` | v0.34.1 | Fake kubernetes clientset |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | v0.34.1 | Scheme, unstructured conversion |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.22.0 | Metrics verification |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10.0 | HTTP test context |\n| `net/http/httptest` | stdlib | HTTP response recording |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Mock Types Required\n\n#### `mockReconcilerStore` (reconciler.Store)\n\nImplements the reconciler's Store interface (different signature from handler.Store):\n\n```go\ntype mockReconcilerStore struct {\n    sandboxes map[string]*handler.SandboxInfo\n    getError  error\n    storeError error\n    updateError error\n    deleteError error\n    listError error\n}\n\nfunc (m *mockReconcilerStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *handler.SandboxInfo) error\nfunc (m *mockReconcilerStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *handler.SandboxInfo) error\nfunc (m *mockReconcilerStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\nfunc (m *mockReconcilerStore) GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*handler.SandboxInfo, error)\nfunc (m *mockReconcilerStore) ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*handler.SandboxInfo, error)\n```\n\n#### `mockMetricsRecorder` (handler.MetricsRecorder)\n\nRecords all metric calls for verification:\n\n```go\ntype mockMetricsRecorder struct {\n    mu              sync.Mutex\n    reconcileTotal  map[string]int       // key: \"resourceType/result\"\n    reconcileDur    []time.Duration\n    reconcileErrors map[string]int       // key: \"resourceType/errorType\"\n    workqueueAdds   map[string]int\n    workqueueDepth  []int\n    gcCleanupTotal  map[string]int\n    gcCleanupDur    map[string]time.Duration\n    gcCleanupErrors map[string]int\n    gcCycleDur      []time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n#### `mockAgentRuntimeLister` (listers.AgentRuntimeLister)\n\n```go\ntype mockAgentRuntimeLister struct {\n    objects map[string]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime  // key: \"namespace/name\"\n    getErr  error\n}\n\nfunc (m *mockAgentRuntimeLister) List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\nfunc (m *mockAgentRuntimeLister) AgentRuntimes(namespace string) listers.AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n```\n\n#### `mockCodeInterpreterLister` (listers.CodeInterpreterLister)\n\nSame pattern as mockAgentRuntimeLister.\n\n#### `mockPodLister` (corev1.PodLister)\n\n```go\ntype mockPodLister struct {\n    objects map[string]*corev1.Pod  // key: \"namespace/name\"\n    getErr  error\n}\n```\n\n#### `mockSandboxReconcilerWatcher` (handler.SandboxReconcilerWatcher)\n\n```go\ntype mockSandboxReconcilerWatcher struct {\n    ch     chan handler.SandboxStatus\n    err    error\n}\n\nfunc (m *mockSandboxReconcilerWatcher) WatchSandboxOnce(namespace, name string) (<-chan handler.SandboxStatus, error)\n```\n\n#### `mockTokenCache` (handler.TokenCache)\n\n```go\ntype mockTokenCache struct {\n    client dynamic.Interface\n    err    error\n}\n\nfunc (m *mockTokenCache) GetOrCreateUserK8sClient(namespace, saName, token string) (dynamic.Interface, error)\n```\n\n#### `mockUserClientFactory` (handler.UserClientFactory)\n\n```go\ntype mockUserClientFactory struct {\n    client dynamic.Interface\n    err    error\n}\n\nfunc (m *mockUserClientFactory) CreateUserClient(token string) (dynamic.Interface, error)\n```\n\n#### `mockInformerFactory` (externalversions.SharedInformerFactory)\n\nFor reconciler tests that need to verify informer registration without starting real informers. Uses embedding of the interface with selective method overrides.\n\n### 2.2 Test Fixtures\n\n#### AgentRuntime fixture builder\n\n```go\nfunc newAgentRuntime(namespace, name string, opts ...arOption) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n```\n\nOptions:\n- `withSessionID(sessionID string)`\n- `withWorkloadName(name string)`\n- `withSandboxName(name string)`\n- `withCondition(condType string, status metav1.ConditionStatus, reason string)`\n- `withDeletionTimestamp(t time.Time)`\n- `withPodTemplate(template *corev1.PodTemplateSpec)`\n- `withPorts(ports []runtimev1alpha1.TargetPort)`\n- `withSessionTimeout(d time.Duration)`\n- `withMaxSessionDuration(d time.Duration)`\n\n#### CodeInterpreter fixture builder\n\n```go\nfunc newCodeInterpreter(namespace, name string, opts ...ciOption) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n```\n\nOptions:\n- `withSessionID(sessionID string)`\n- `withWarmPoolSize(size int32)`\n- `withAuthMode(mode runtimev1alpha1.AuthMode)`\n- `withCondition(...)` (same as AgentRuntime)\n- `withDeletionTimestamp(t time.Time)`\n- `withTemplate(tmpl runtimev1alpha1.CITemplate)`\n\n#### Pod fixture builder\n\n```go\nfunc newPod(namespace, name string, opts ...podOption) *corev1.Pod\n```\n\nOptions:\n- `withSandboxName(name string)`\n- `withPhase(phase corev1.PodPhase)`\n- `withPodIP(ip string)`\n- `withOwnerRef(kind, name string)`\n\n#### SandboxInfo fixture builder\n\n```go\nfunc newSandboxInfo(sessionID string, opts ...sandboxInfoOption) *handler.SandboxInfo\n```\n\n### 2.3 Key Interface Signatures\n\n#### handler.Store (used by create/delete/lifecycle handlers)\n\n| Method | Signature |\n|--------|-----------|\n| `StoreSandbox` | `(ctx, info *SandboxInfo) error` — no sessionID param |\n| `UpdateSandbox` | `(ctx, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo) error` |\n| `GetSandbox` | `(ctx, sessionID string) (*SandboxInfo, error)` |\n| `DeleteSandbox` | `(ctx, sessionID string) error` |\n| `ListSandboxes` | `(ctx) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)` — returns slice |\n\n#### reconciler.Store (used by SandboxReconciler)\n\n| Method | Signature |\n|--------|-----------|\n| `StoreSandbox` | `(ctx, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo) error` — has sessionID param |\n| `UpdateSandbox` | `(ctx, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo) error` |\n| `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `(ctx, sessionID string) error` — different name |\n| `GetSandbox` | `(ctx, sessionID string) (*SandboxInfo, error)` |\n| `ListSandboxes` | `(ctx) (map[string]*SandboxInfo, error)` — returns map |\n\n**Critical**: Tests must use the correct mock for the correct interface. The existing `mockStore` in `sandbox_delete_test.go` implements `handler.Store`, not `reconciler.Store`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 HTTP Handler Contracts (sandbox_create.go)\n\n#### `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox`\n\n| Scenario | Request | Response | Side Effects |\n|----------|---------|----------|--------------|\n| Success | `POST /v1/agent-runtime` with `{\"name\":\"ar-1\",\"namespace\":\"default\"}` | `200 OK` with `{sessionId, sandboxId, sandboxName, entryPoints}` | StoreSandbox → Create CR → Wait → UpdateSandbox |\n| Invalid JSON | Malformed body | `400 Bad Request` | None |\n| Validation fail | `{\"name\":\"\",\"namespace\":\"\"}` | `400 Bad Request` with error message | None |\n| Template not found | Valid request, no AR in informer | `404 Not Found` | None |\n| Missing podTemplate | AR exists but `spec.template == nil` | `400 Bad Request` \"podTemplate is required\" | None |\n| Store failure | StoreSandbox returns error | `500 Internal Server Error` | None |\n| Watcher failure | WatchSandboxOnce returns error | `500 Internal Server Error` | StoreSandbox already called |\n| Dynamic client error | getDynamicClient fails | `401 Unauthorized` | StoreSandbox already called |\n| CR creation fails | dynamic.Create returns error | `500 Internal Server Error` | StoreSandbox already called |\n| Watch timeout | 2-minute deadline exceeded | `500 Internal Server Error` \"sandbox creation timed out\" | CR rolled back |\n| Watch error | Channel receives error | `500 Internal Server Error` with error message | CR rolled back |\n| Non-running status | Channel receives status != \"running\" | `500 Internal Server Error` \"sandbox creation timed out\" | CR rolled back |\n| PodIP resolution fails | resolvePodIP returns error | `500 Internal Server Error` | CR rolled back |\n\n#### `CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox`\n\nSame scenarios as AgentRuntime, plus:\n\n| Scenario | Request | Response | Notes |\n|----------|---------|----------|-------|\n| WarmPool > 0 | CI with `warmPoolSize: 3` | Creates `SandboxClaim` CR | GVR = SandboxClaimGVR, Kind = SandboxClaimsKind |\n| WarmPool = 0 | CI with `warmPoolSize: 0` or nil | Creates `Sandbox` CR | GVR = SandboxGVR, Kind = SandboxesKind |\n| AuthMode = PicoD | CI with `authMode: picod` | Injects PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env | Fetches secret from K8s |\n| Secret not found | PicoD mode, secret missing | `401 Unauthorized` \"public key not yet loaded\" | |\n| Missing template | CI exists but template == nil | `400 Bad Request` \"template is required\" | |\n\n#### `getDynamicClient`\n\n| Scenario | enableAuth | Authorization header | Result |\n|----------|-----------|---------------------|--------|\n| Auth disabled | false | — | Returns h.dynamicClient |\n| Auth enabled, no token | true | missing | Error \"authorization token is required\" |\n| Auth enabled, Bearer token | true | \"Bearer xyz\" | Strips \"Bearer \", uses tokenCache or userClientFactory |\n| Auth enabled, raw token | true | \"xyz\" | Uses token as-is |\n| No cache or factory | true | \"Bearer xyz\" | Error \"no user client factory available\" |\n\n### 3.2 CR Builder Contracts\n\n#### `buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR`\n\n| Input | Output CR |\n|-------|-----------|\n| AgentRuntime with session-id label, workload-name, sandbox-name | `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1 Sandbox` with labels, annotations, spec |\n| AgentRuntime with `sessionTimeout: 30m` | Annotation `idle-timeout: \"30m\"` |\n| AgentRuntime with `maxSessionDuration: 24h` | Spec lifecycle `shutdownTime` = now + 24h |\n| AgentRuntime with ports `[{name:\"http\", port:8080, protocol:\"HTTP\"}]` | Spec ports array |\n| AgentRuntime with podTemplate | Spec podTemplate (converted to unstructured) |\n\n#### `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR`\n\n| Input | Output CR |\n|-------|-----------|\n| CI with `warmPoolSize: 0` | `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1 Sandbox` |\n| CI with `warmPoolSize: 3` | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1 SandboxClaim` (no spec) |\n| CI with `authMode: picod` | Same as above, caller injects auth env separately |\n\n### 3.3 Reconciler Contracts\n\n#### `NewSandboxReconciler`\n\n| Condition | Result |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Store = nil | `panic(\"Store is required\")` |\n| Clientset = nil | `panic(\"Clientset is required\")` |\n| InformerFactory = nil | `panic(\"InformerFactory is required\")` |\n| Workers = 0 | Defaults to `defaultWorkers` (2) |\n| All valid | Returns reconciler with event handlers registered |\n\n#### `syncHandler`\n\n| Key | Resource Found | Result |\n|-----|---------------|--------|\n| `\"ns/name\"` | AgentRuntime exists | Calls `reconcileAgentRuntime` |\n| `\"ns/name\"` | CodeInterpreter exists | Calls `reconcileCodeInterpreter` |\n| `\"ns/name\"` | Pod exists (with sandbox-name label) | Calls `reconcilePod` |\n| `\"ns/name\"` | None found | Returns nil (no-op) |\n| `\"invalid-key\"` | — | Error \"invalid key\" |\n| `\"ns/name\"` | Lister error (non-NotFound) | Error with metrics recording |\n\n#### `reconcileAgentRuntime`\n\n| AR State | Store State | Action |\n|----------|-------------|--------|\n| Missing session-id label | — | Log + return nil |\n| DeletionTimestamp set | Sandbox exists | DeleteSandboxBySessionID |\n| Not found in store | — | StoreSandbox with initial info |\n| Found in store, status changed (pending→running) | Status differs | UpdateSandbox |\n| Found in store, status = terminated | Status = terminated | UpdateSandbox + DeleteSandboxBySessionID |\n| Not found in K8s (IsNotFound) | — | Return nil (already cleaned up) |\n| Lister error | — | Error with metrics |\n\n#### `reconcileCodeInterpreter`\n\nSame patterns as reconcileAgentRuntime, plus:\n- WarmPoolSize > 0: logs activation message\n\n#### `reconcilePod`\n\n| Pod State | Store State | Action |\n|-----------|-------------|--------|\n| Missing sandbox-name label | — | Return nil |\n| Phase != Running or PodIP empty | — | Return nil |\n| No matching sandbox in store | — | Return nil |\n| PodIP already matches | — | Return nil |\n| PodIP changed | Sandbox found | UpdateSandbox with new PodIP + EntryPoints |\n| Store ListSandboxes error | — | Error with metrics |\n\n#### `WatchSandboxOnce`\n\n| Scenario | Channel Result |\n|----------|---------------|\n| AR found with Ready=True | `{Status: \"running\"}` |\n| AR found with Ready=False | `{Status: \"pending\"}` |\n| CI found with Ready=True | `{Status: \"running\"}` |\n| Neither AR nor CI found within 2 min | `{Error: \"watch timeout\"}` |\n\n### 3.4 Event Handler Contracts\n\n| Event | Condition | Enqueued |\n|-------|-----------|----------|\n| AgentRuntime Add | Any | Yes, with metrics |\n| AgentRuntime Update | Any | Yes, with metrics |\n| AgentRuntime Delete | Normal object | Yes, with metrics |\n| AgentRuntime Delete | Tombstone (DeletedFinalStateUnknown) | Yes, extracts real obj |\n| CodeInterpreter Add | Any | Yes, with metrics |\n| CodeInterpreter Update | Any | Yes, with metrics |\n| CodeInterpreter Delete | Normal/Tombstone | Yes, with metrics |\n| Pod Add | Has sandbox-name label | Yes, with metrics |\n| Pod Add | No sandbox-name label | No enqueue |\n| Pod Update | Was not running, now running | Yes, with metrics |\n| Pod Update | IP changed | Yes, with metrics |\n| Pod Update | No change in running/IP | No enqueue |\n| Pod Update | No sandbox-name label | No enqueue |\n| Pod Delete | Any | Log only (no enqueue) |\n\n### 3.5 Utility Function Contracts\n\n#### `mapConditionToStatus`\n\n| Conditions | Result |\n|------------|--------|\n| Empty | `\"pending\"` |\n| Ready=True | `\"running\"` |\n| Ready=False, Reason=Terminated | `\"terminated\"` |\n| Ready=False, other reason | `\"pending\"` |\n| Ready=Unknown | `\"pending\"` |\n| No Ready condition | `\"pending\"` |\n\n#### `isNotFoundError`\n\n| Error | Result |\n|-------|--------|\n| nil | false |\n| `\"sandbox not found\"` | true |\n| `apierrors.IsNotFound(err)` | true |\n| Other error | false |\n\n#### `buildEntryPointsFromSandboxInfo`\n\n| Input | Output |\n|-------|--------|\n| EntryPoints with `Endpoint: \"10.0.0.1:8080\"`, PodIP `\"10.0.0.2\"` | Endpoint `\"10.0.0.2:8080\"` (IP replaced, port preserved) |\n\n#### `extractPort`\n\n| Input | Output |\n|-------|--------|\n| `\"10.0.0.1:8080\"` | `\"8080\"` |\n| `\"8080\"` | `\"8080\"` |\n| `\"\"` | `\"\"` |\n\n#### `getPortsOrDefaults`\n\n| Input | Output |\n|-------|--------|\n| Empty slice | `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: HTTP, PathPrefix: \"/\"}]` |\n| Non-empty | Input as-is |\n\n#### `buildEntryPoints`\n\n| Input | Output |\n|-------|--------|\n| PodIP `\"10.0.0.1\"`, ports `[{Port:8080, Protocol:\"HTTP\", PathPrefix:\"/\"}]` | `[{Path:\"/\", Protocol:\"HTTP\", Endpoint:\"10.0.0.1:8080\"}]` |\n\n#### `injectPicodAuthEnv`\n\n| Scenario | Result |\n|----------|--------|\n| Secret exists with public.pem | Injects PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env into first container |\n| Secret not found | Error \"public key not yet loaded from Router Secret\" |\n| Secret exists but no public.pem | Error \"public key not yet loaded from Router Secret\" |\n| CR has no spec | Error \"spec not found in CR\" |\n| CR has no podTemplate | Error \"podTemplate not found in spec\" |\n| CR has no containers | Error \"containers not found in podTemplate\" |\n\n#### `resolvePodIP`\n\n| Strategy | Condition | Result |\n|----------|-----------|--------|\n| Direct pod get by sandboxName | Pod exists, Running, has IP | Return PodIP |\n| Annotation lookup | `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` annotation set | Get pod by annotation name |\n| Label selector | List pods by `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name` label | Find pod with matching ownerRef |\n| All fail | — | Error \"pod not found for sandbox\" |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Error Classification\n\n| Component | Error Source | Test Strategy |\n|-----------|-------------|---------------|\n| handler.Store | StoreSandbox/UpdateSandbox/DeleteSandbox returns error | Mock store with configurable error injection |\n| reconciler.Store | Same as above, plus ListSandboxes error | mockReconcilerStore with error fields |\n| Dynamic client | Create/Delete returns API error | Fake dynamic client with reactor errors |\n| KubeClientset | Get/List Pods/Secrets returns error | Fake kubernetes client with reactor errors |\n| Lister | Get/List returns not-found or other error | Mock lister with configurable getErr |\n| Watcher | WatchSandboxOnce returns error or timeout | Mock watcher with configurable channel behavior |\n| TokenCache/UserClientFactory | Client creation fails | Mock with configurable err |\n| MetricsRecorder | Nil receiver | Nil-safety tests (assert.NotPanics) |\n\n### 4.2 Rollback Verification\n\nFor sandbox creation, tests must verify that `rollbackCR` is called on failure paths:\n- Watch timeout\n- Watch error\n- Non-running status\n- PodIP resolution failure\n\nThe mock dynamic client should track Delete calls to verify rollback.\n\n### 4.3 Metrics Verification\n\nEach error path in reconciler code should verify that the correct metric is incremented:\n- `IncReconcileErrors(resourceType, errorType)` on lister/store failures\n- `IncReconcileTotal(resourceType, resultError)` on sync failure\n- `IncReconcileTotal(resourceType, resultSuccess)` on sync success\n- `IncWorkqueueAdds(resourceType)` on event handler enqueue\n\n---\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Test Categories\n\n| Category | Scope | Files |\n|----------|-------|-------|\n| Handler unit tests | HTTP request/response, business logic | `sandbox_create_test.go`, `sandbox_create_helpers_test.go` |\n| Reconciler unit tests | Sync loop, reconciliation logic | `reconciler_test.go`, `sync_test.go` |\n| Resource-specific reconciler tests | AR, CI, Pod reconciliation | `agentruntime_test.go`, `codeinterpreter_test.go`, `pod_test.go` |\n| Event handler tests | Add/Update/Delete event processing | `event_handlers_test.go` |\n| Utility function tests | Pure functions, builders | `sandbox_create_helpers_test.go`, `pod_test.go` |\n| Model tests | Validation, serialization | `models_test.go` |\n| Nil-safety tests | Nil receiver protection | Each test file |\n\n### 5.2 Detailed Test Plan\n\n#### `sandbox_create_test.go` — SandboxCreateHandler\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `TestNewSandboxCreateHandler_AllFieldsSet` | NewSandboxCreateHandler | Verifies all deps are copied to handler struct |\n| 2 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_InvalidJSON` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | Malformed JSON → 400 |\n| 3 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_MissingName` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | Empty name → 400 |\n| 4 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_MissingNamespace` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | Empty namespace → 400 |\n| 5 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_TemplateNotFound` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | Lister returns NotFound → 404 |\n| 6 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_MissingPodTemplate` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | AR exists but no template → 400 |\n| 7 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_StoreFails` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | StoreSandbox error → 500 |\n| 8 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_WatcherFails` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | WatchSandboxOnce error → 500 |\n| 9 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_AuthDisabled_Success` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | Full happy path, auth disabled |\n| 10 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_AuthEnabled_Success` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | Full happy path, auth enabled with Bearer token |\n| 11 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_AuthEnabled_NoToken` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | Auth enabled, no header → 401 |\n| 12 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_CRCreateFails` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | Dynamic client Create error → 500 |\n| 13 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_WatchTimeout` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | 2-min deadline exceeded → 500, rollback |\n| 14 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_WatchError` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | Channel receives error → 500, rollback |\n| 15 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_NonRunningStatus` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | Status != \"running\" → 500, rollback |\n| 16 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_PodIPResolutionFails` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | resolvePodIP error → 500, rollback |\n| 17 | `TestCreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_UpdateStoreFails` | CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox | UpdateSandbox error (logged, not returned) |\n| 18 | `TestCreateCodeInterpreterSandbox_InvalidJSON` | CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox | Malformed JSON → 400 |\n| 19 | `TestCreateCodeInterpreterSandbox_TemplateNotFound` | CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox | CI not in lister → 404 |\n| 20 | `TestCreateCodeInterpreterSandbox_MissingTemplate` | CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox | CI exists, template nil → 400 |\n| 21 | `TestCreateCodeInterpreterSandbox_WarmPool_SandboxClaim` | CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox | warmPoolSize > 0 → SandboxClaim CR |\n| 22 | `TestCreateCodeInterpreterSandbox_NoWarmPool_Sandbox` | CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox | warmPoolSize = 0 → Sandbox CR |\n| 23 | `TestCreateCodeInterpreterSandbox_PicoDAuth_Success` | CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox | AuthMode=PicoD, secret exists → inject env |\n| 24 | `TestCreateCodeInterpreterSandbox_PicoDAuth_SecretMissing` | CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox | AuthMode=PicoD, secret not found → 401 |\n| 25 | `TestCreateCodeInterpreterSandbox_FullSuccess` | CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox | Full happy path |\n| 26 | `TestGetDynamicClient_AuthDisabled` | getDynamicClient | Returns default client |\n| 27 | `TestGetDynamicClient_AuthEnabled_BearerToken` | getDynamicClient | Strips Bearer prefix, uses tokenCache |\n| 28 | `TestGetDynamicClient_AuthEnabled_RawToken` | getDynamicClient | Uses raw token with userClientFactory |\n| 29 | `TestGetDynamicClient_NoFactory` | getDynamicClient | Neither cache nor factory → error |\n| 30 | `TestGetDynamicClient_MissingAuthHeader` | getDynamicClient | Empty Authorization → error |\n| 31 | `TestRollbackCR_Success` | rollbackCR | Deletes CR successfully |\n| 32 | `TestRollbackCR_NotFound` | rollbackCR | NotFound error → returns nil (idempotent) |\n| 33 | `TestRollbackCR_OtherError` | rollbackCR | Other error → returned |\n\n#### `sandbox_create_helpers_test.go` — Helper Functions\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `TestBuildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR_Basic` | buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR | Minimal AR → valid CR with labels |\n| 2 | `TestBuildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR_WithSessionTimeout` | buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR | sessionTimeout → idle-timeout annotation |\n| 3 | `TestBuildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR_WithMaxDuration` | buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR | maxSessionDuration → shutdownTime |\n| 4 | `TestBuildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR_WithPorts` | buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR | Ports in spec |\n| 5 | `TestBuildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR_WithPodTemplate` | buildAgentRuntimeSandboxCR | PodTemplate converted to unstructured |\n| 6 | `TestBuildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR_WarmPoolZero` | buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR | warmPoolSize=0 → Sandbox CR with spec |\n| 7 | `TestBuildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR_WarmPoolThree` | buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR | warmPoolSize=3 → SandboxClaim, no spec |\n| 8 | `TestBuildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR_WithTemplate` | buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR | CI template → container spec |\n| 9 | `TestBuildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR_WithRuntimeClass` | buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR | RuntimeClassName set |\n| 10 | `TestBuildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR_WithImagePullSecrets` | buildCodeInterpreterSandboxCR | ImagePullSecrets set |\n| 11 | `TestGetPortsOrDefaults_Empty` | getPortsOrDefaults | Returns default 8080/HTTP |\n| 12 | `TestGetPortsOrDefaults_NonEmpty` | getPortsOrDefaults | Returns input as-is |\n| 13 | `TestInjectPicodAuthEnv_Success` | injectPicodAuthEnv | Injects env into first container |\n| 14 | `TestInjectPicodAuthEnv_AppendsToExistingEnv` | injectPicodAuthEnv | Preserves existing env vars |\n| 15 | `TestInjectPicodAuthEnv_SecretNotFound` | injectPicodAuthEnv | Returns error |\n| 16 | `TestInjectPicodAuthEnv_NoPublicKey` | injectPicodAuthEnv | Returns error |\n| 17 | `TestInjectPicodAuthEnv_NoSpec` | injectPicodAuthEnv | Returns error |\n| 18 | `TestInjectPicodAuthEnv_NoPodTemplate` | injectPicodAuthEnv | Returns error |\n| 19 | `TestInjectPicodAuthEnv_NoContainers` | injectPicodAuthEnv | Returns error |\n| 20 | `TestResolvePodIP_DirectGet` | resolvePodIP | Pod found by name, running, has IP |\n| 21 | `TestResolvePodIP_AnnotationLookup` | resolvePodIP | Pod found via annotation |\n| 22 | `TestResolvePodIP_LabelSelector` | resolvePodIP | Pod found via label + ownerRef |\n| 23 | `TestResolvePodIP_NotRunning` | resolvePodIP | Pod exists but not running → error |\n| 24 | `TestResolvePodIP_NoIP` | resolvePodIP | Pod running but no IP → error |\n| 25 | `TestResolvePodIP_NotFound` | resolvePodIP | No pod found → error |\n| 26 | `TestBuildEntryPoints_SinglePort` | buildEntryPoints | One port → one entry point |\n| 27 | `TestBuildEntryPoints_MultiplePorts` | buildEntryPoints | Multiple ports → multiple entry points |\n| 28 | `TestBuildEntryPoints_EmptyPorts` | buildEntryPoints | Empty → empty result |\n| 29 | `TestGenerateSessionID_IsUUID` | generateSessionID | Returns valid UUID format |\n| 30 | `TestGenerateSandboxName_Format` | generateSandboxName | Format: `{workloadName}-{8 random chars}` |\n| 31 | `TestRandString_Length` | RandString | Returns string of requested length |\n| 32 | `TestRandString_Charset` | RandString | Only contains allowed charset chars |\n\n#### `models_test.go` — Data Models\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `TestCreateSandboxRequest_Validate_Valid` | Validate | Valid request passes |\n| 2 | `TestCreateSandboxRequest_Validate_InvalidKind` | Validate | Invalid kind → error |\n| 3 | `TestCreateSandboxRequest_Validate_EmptyName` | Validate | Empty name → error |\n| 4 | `TestCreateSandboxRequest_Validate_EmptyNamespace` | Validate | Empty namespace → error |\n| 5 | `TestCreateSandboxRequest_Validate_AllEmpty` | Validate | All empty → error mentions all fields |\n| 6 | `TestCreateSandboxResponse_JSONSerialization` | JSON marshal/unmarshal | Round-trip serialization |\n| 7 | `TestSandboxInfo_JSONSerialization` | JSON marshal/unmarshal | Full struct round-trip |\n| 8 | `TestEntryPoint_JSONSerialization` | JSON marshal/unmarshal | Round-trip |\n| 9 | `TestSandboxStatus_WithError` | SandboxInfo | Error field set |\n| 10 | `TestSandboxStatus_WithStatus` | SandboxInfo | Status field set |\n\n#### `reconciler/fixtures_test.go` — Shared Test Infrastructure\n\nContains all mock types and fixture builders described in Section 2.\n\n#### `reconciler_test.go` — SandboxReconciler Core\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `TestNewSandboxReconciler_NilStore_Panics` | NewSandboxReconciler | Store=nil → panic |\n| 2 | `TestNewSandboxReconciler_NilClientset_Panics` | NewSandboxReconciler | Clientset=nil → panic |\n| 3 | `TestNewSandboxReconciler_NilInformerFactory_Panics` | NewSandboxReconciler | InformerFactory=nil → panic |\n| 4 | `TestNewSandboxReconciler_DefaultWorkers` | NewSandboxReconciler | Workers=0 → defaults to 2 |\n| 5 | `TestNewSandboxReconciler_CustomWorkers` | NewSandboxReconciler | Workers=5 → uses 5 |\n| 6 | `TestNewSandboxReconciler_WithMetricsRecorder` | NewSandboxReconciler | MetricsRecorder set |\n| 7 | `TestNewSandboxReconciler_EventHandlersRegistered` | registerEventHandlers | Verifies informers have event handlers |\n| 8 | `TestEnqueue_WithNamespace` | Enqueue | Key = \"ns/name\", metrics recorded |\n| 9 | `TestEnqueue_WithoutNamespace` | Enqueue | Key = \"name\", metrics recorded |\n| 10 | `TestEnqueue_NilMetricsRecorder` | Enqueue | No panic with nil metrics |\n| 11 | `TestRun_DuplicateCall_Ignored` | Run | Second Run call logs and returns |\n| 12 | `TestWatchSandboxOnce_ARFound_Running` | WatchSandboxOnce | AR with Ready=True → \"running\" |\n| 13 | `TestWatchSandboxOnce_ARFound_Pending` | WatchSandboxOnce | AR with Ready=False → \"pending\" |\n| 14 | `TestWatchSandboxOnce_CIFound_Running` | WatchSandboxOnce | CI with Ready=True → \"running\" |\n| 15 | `TestWatchSandboxOnce_NotFound_Timeout` | WatchSandboxOnce | Neither found → timeout error |\n| 16 | `TestWatchSandboxOnce_WithNamespace` | WatchSandboxOnce | Namespace included in key |\n\n#### `sync_test.go` — Sync Loop\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `TestSyncHandler_AgentRuntimeFound` | syncHandler | AR exists → calls reconcileAgentRuntime |\n| 2 | `TestSyncHandler_CodeInterpreterFound` | syncHandler | CI exists → calls reconcileCodeInterpreter |\n| 3 | `TestSyncHandler_PodFound` | syncHandler | Pod exists → calls reconcilePod |\n| 4 | `TestSyncHandler_NoneFound` | syncHandler | Nothing found → nil |\n| 5 | `TestSyncHandler_InvalidKey` | syncHandler | Bad key format → error |\n| 6 | `TestSyncHandler_ARListerError` | syncHandler | Lister error → error with metrics |\n| 7 | `TestSyncHandler_CIListerError` | syncHandler | Lister error → error with metrics |\n| 8 | `TestProcessNextWorkItem_Success` | processNextWorkItem | Valid key, no error → Forget + Done |\n| 9 | `TestProcessNextWorkItem_Error_Retry` | processNextWorkItem | Error → AddRateLimited + Done |\n| 10 | `TestProcessNextWorkItem_Error_MaxRetries` | processNextWorkItem | 15+ retries → Forget + HandleError |\n| 11 | `TestProcessNextWorkItem_InvalidObjectType` | processNextWorkItem | Non-string item → Done + Forget |\n| 12 | `TestProcessNextWorkItem_MetricsRecorded` | processNextWorkItem | Duration and total metrics recorded |\n| 13 | `TestProcessNextWorkItem_Shutdown` | processNextWorkItem | Queue shutdown → returns false |\n| 14 | `TestDetermineResourceType_AgentRuntime` | determineResourceType | AR exists → \"agentruntime\" |\n| 15 | `TestDetermineResourceType_CodeInterpreter` | determineResourceType | CI exists → \"codeinterpreter\" |\n| 16 | `TestDetermineResourceType_Pod` | determineResourceType | Neither → \"pod\" |\n| 17 | `TestDetermineResourceType_InvalidKey` | determineResourceType | Bad key → \"agentruntime\" default |\n| 18 | `TestRunWorker_ProcessesItems` | runWorker | Processes until queue empty |\n\n#### `agentruntime_test.go` — AgentRuntime Reconciliation\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_InvalidKey` | reconcileAgentRuntime | Bad key → error |\n| 2 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_NotFound` | reconcileAgentRuntime | IsNotFound → nil (cleanup) |\n| 3 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_ListerError` | reconcileAgentRuntime | Lister error → error + metrics |\n| 4 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_MissingSessionID` | reconcileAgentRuntime | No session-id label → log + nil |\n| 5 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_DeletionTimestamp` | reconcileAgentRuntime | Being deleted → DeleteSandboxBySessionID |\n| 6 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_DeletionTimestamp_StoreError` | reconcileAgentRuntime | Delete fails → error + metrics |\n| 7 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_NewSandbox` | reconcileAgentRuntime | Not in store → StoreSandbox |\n| 8 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_NewSandbox_StoreError` | reconcileAgentRuntime | StoreSandbox fails → error + metrics |\n| 9 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_StatusUpdate_PendingToRunning` | reconcileAgentRuntime | Status changed → UpdateSandbox |\n| 10 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_StatusUpdate_RunningToTerminated` | reconcileAgentRuntime | Terminated → UpdateSandbox + DeleteSandboxBySessionID |\n| 11 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_StatusUpdate_Terminated_DeleteFails` | reconcileAgentRuntime | Delete after termination fails → error |\n| 12 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_StatusUpdate_UpdateFails` | reconcileAgentRuntime | UpdateSandbox error → error + metrics |\n| 13 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_NoStatusChange` | reconcileAgentRuntime | Status same → no store call |\n| 14 | `TestReconcileAgentRuntime_GetSandboxError` | reconcileAgentRuntime | GetSandbox non-NotFound error → error + metrics |\n| 15 | `TestMapConditionToStatus_Empty` | mapConditionToStatus | No conditions → \"pending\" |\n| 16 | `TestMapConditionToStatus_ReadyTrue` | mapConditionToStatus | Ready=True → \"running\" |\n| 17 | `TestMapConditionToStatus_ReadyFalse_Terminated` | mapConditionToStatus | Ready=False, Terminated → \"terminated\" |\n| 18 | `TestMapConditionToStatus_ReadyFalse_Other` | mapConditionToStatus | Ready=False, other → \"pending\" |\n| 19 | `TestMapConditionToStatus_ReadyUnknown` | mapConditionToStatus | Ready=Unknown → \"pending\" |\n| 20 | `TestMapConditionToStatus_NoReadyCondition` | mapConditionToStatus | Other condition type → \"pending\" |\n| 21 | `TestIsNotFoundError_Nil` | isNotFoundError | nil → false |\n| 22 | `TestIsNotFoundError_SandboxNotFound` | isNotFoundError | \"sandbox not found\" → true |\n| 23 | `TestIsNotFoundError_APINotFound` | isNotFoundError | apierrors.IsNotFound → true |\n| 24 | `TestIsNotFoundError_Other` | isNotFoundError | Other error → false |\n\n#### `codeinterpreter_test.go` — CodeInterpreter Reconciliation\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `TestReconcileCodeInterpreter_InvalidKey` | reconcileCodeInterpreter | Bad key → error |\n| 2 | `TestReconcileCodeInterpreter_NotFound` | reconcileCodeInterpreter | IsNotFound → nil |\n| 3 | `TestReconcileCodeInterpreter_ListerError` | reconcileCodeInterpreter | Lister error → error + metrics |\n| 4 | `TestReconcileCodeInterpreter_MissingSessionID` | reconcileCodeInterpreter | No session-id label → log + nil |\n| 5 | `TestReconcileCodeInterpreter_DeletionTimestamp` | reconcileCodeInterpreter | Being deleted → DeleteSandboxBySessionID |\n| 6 | `TestReconcileCodeInterpreter_NewSandbox` | reconcileCodeInterpreter | Not in store → StoreSandbox |\n| 7 | `TestReconcileCodeInterpreter_StatusUpdate` | reconcileCodeInterpreter | Status changed → UpdateSandbox |\n| 8 | `TestReconcileCodeInterpreter_Terminated` | reconcileCodeInterpreter | Terminated → UpdateSandbox + DeleteSandboxBySessionID |\n| 9 | `TestReconcileCodeInterpreter_NoStatusChange` | reconcileCodeInterpreter | Status same → no store call |\n| 10 | `TestReconcileCodeInterpreter_WarmPoolActive` | reconcileCodeInterpreter | WarmPoolSize > 0 → log message |\n| 11 | `TestReconcileCodeInterpreter_WarmPoolNil` | reconcileCodeInterpreter | WarmPoolSize nil → no warm pool log |\n\n#### `pod_test.go` — Pod Reconciliation\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `TestReconcilePod_InvalidKey` | reconcilePod | Bad key → error |\n| 2 | `TestReconcilePod_NotFound` | reconcilePod | IsNotFound → nil |\n| 3 | `TestReconcilePod_ListerError` | reconcilePod | Lister error → error + metrics |\n| 4 | `TestReconcilePod_NoSandboxLabel` | reconcilePod | No sandbox-name label → nil |\n| 5 | `TestReconcilePod_NotRunning` | reconcilePod | Phase != Running → nil |\n| 6 | `TestReconcilePod_NoPodIP` | reconcilePod | Running but no IP → nil |\n| 7 | `TestReconcilePod_NoMatchingSandbox` | reconcilePod | No sandbox in store → nil |\n| 8 | `TestReconcilePod_PodIPAlreadyMatches` | reconcilePod | Same IP → nil |\n| 9 | `TestReconcilePod_PodIPChanged` | reconcilePod | IP changed → UpdateSandbox with new IP + EntryPoints |\n| 10 | `TestReconcilePod_ListSandboxesError` | reconcilePod | Store error → error + metrics |\n| 11 | `TestReconcilePod_UpdateSandboxError` | reconcilePod | Update fails → error + metrics |\n| 12 | `TestBuildEntryPointsFromSandboxInfo` | buildEntryPointsFromSandboxInfo | Replaces IP, preserves port |\n| 13 | `TestBuildEntryPointsFromSandboxInfo_Empty` | buildEntryPointsFromSandboxInfo | No entry points → empty result |\n| 14 | `TestExtractPort_WithPort` | extractPort | `\"10.0.0.1:8080\"` → `\"8080\"` |\n| 15 | `TestExtractPort_NoPort` | extractPort | `\"8080\"` → `\"8080\"` |\n| 16 | `TestExtractPort_Empty` | extractPort | `\"\"` → `\"\"` |\n\n#### `event_handlers_test.go` — Event Handlers\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `TestOnAgentRuntimeAdd_ValidObject` | onAgentRuntimeAdd | Enqueues key, records metrics |\n| 2 | `TestOnAgentRuntimeAdd_InvalidKey` | onAgentRuntimeAdd | MetaNamespaceKeyFunc fails → logs, no enqueue |\n| 3 | `TestOnAgentRuntimeUpdate_ValidObject` | onAgentRuntimeUpdate | Enqueues key from newObj |\n| 4 | `TestOnAgentRuntimeDelete_Normal` | onAgentRuntimeDelete | Enqueues key |\n| 5 | `TestOnAgentRuntimeDelete_Tombstone` | onAgentRuntimeDelete | DeletedFinalStateUnknown → extracts real obj |\n| 6 | `TestOnCodeInterpreterAdd_ValidObject` | onCodeInterpreterAdd | Enqueues key, records metrics |\n| 7 | `TestOnCodeInterpreterUpdate_ValidObject` | onCodeInterpreterUpdate | Enqueues key from newObj |\n| 8 | `TestOnCodeInterpreterDelete_Normal` | onCodeInterpreterDelete | Enqueues key |\n| 9 | `TestOnCodeInterpreterDelete_Tombstone` | onCodeInterpreterDelete | Tombstone handling |\n| 10 | `TestOnPodAdd_WithSandboxLabel` | onPodAdd | Has sandbox-name label → enqueue |\n| 11 | `TestOnPodAdd_NoSandboxLabel` | onPodAdd | No sandbox-name label → no enqueue |\n| 12 | `TestOnPodAdd_InvalidType` | onPodAdd | Non-Pod object → no enqueue |\n| 13 | `TestOnPodUpdate_NotRunningToRunning` | onPodUpdate | Phase change → enqueue |\n| 14 | `TestOnPodUpdate_IPChanged` | onPodUpdate | IP changed → enqueue |\n| 15 | `TestOnPodUpdate_NoChange` | onPodUpdate | No relevant change → no enqueue |\n| 16 | `TestOnPodUpdate_NoSandboxLabel` | onPodUpdate | No sandbox-name label → no enqueue |\n| 17 | `TestOnPodUpdate_InvalidType` | onPodUpdate | Non-Pod objects → no enqueue |\n| 18 | `TestOnPodDelete_Normal` | onPodDelete | Logs deletion, no enqueue |\n| 19 | `TestOnPodDelete_Tombstone` | onPodDelete | Tombstone handling |\n| 20 | `TestOnPodDelete_InvalidType` | onPodDelete | Non-Pod → no log |\n| 21 | `TestEventHandlers_NilMetricsRecorder` | All handlers | No panic with nil metrics |\n\n### 5.3 Mocking Strategy\n\n| Dependency | Mock Approach | Rationale |\n|-----------|---------------|-----------|\n| `Store` (handler) | Inline struct with configurable errors | Already tested in sandbox_delete_test.go |\n| `Store` (reconciler) | `mockReconcilerStore` with error injection fields | Different signature, needs separate mock |\n| `MetricsRecorder` | `mockMetricsRecorder` with call counters | Verifies correct metrics are recorded |\n| `AgentRuntimeLister` | Map-backed mock with getErr injection | Avoids real informer setup |\n| `CodeInterpreterLister` | Map-backed mock with getErr injection | Same pattern |\n| `PodLister` | Map-backed mock with getErr injection | Same pattern |\n| `dynamic.Interface` | `dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient` with reactors | Standard K8s fake client |\n| `kubernetes.Interface` | `kubefake.NewSimpleClientset` | Standard K8s fake clientset |\n| `SandboxReconcilerWatcher` | Mock with pre-configured channel behavior | Controls watch timing/results |\n| `TokenCache` | Mock with configurable client/error | Isolates auth logic |\n| `UserClientFactory` | Mock with configurable client/error | Isolates client creation |\n| `SharedInformerFactory` | Partial mock (interface embedding) | Only need AddEventHandler verification |\n| `workqueue.RateLimitingInterface` | `workqueue.NewNamedRateLimitingQueue` (real) | Real queue is simple enough |\n\n### 5.4 Test Execution\n\n```bash\n# Run all workloadmanager tests\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v -count=1\n\n# Run handler tests only\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handler/... -v -count=1\n\n# Run reconciler tests only\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/... -v -count=1\n\n# Run with coverage\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -coverprofile=coverage.out -count=1\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n\n# Target: >80% statement coverage for pkg/workloadmanager\n```\n\n### 5.5 Coverage Targets\n\n| Sub-package | Current | Target |\n|-------------|---------|--------|\n| `handler/` | ~45% (delete + lifecycle) | >85% |\n| `reconciler/` | ~15% (metrics only) | >80% |\n| `response/` | ~95% | Maintain |\n| **Overall** | ~35% | >80% |\n\n### 5.6 Risk Areas\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|\n| `sandbox_create.go` has long methods with many branches | Test each branch independently with focused mocks |\n| Reconciler uses real informers internally | Use mock informer factory that only registers handlers; test sync logic separately from informer lifecycle |\n| `WatchSandboxOnce` uses goroutines with polling | Test channel behavior with mock listers; verify timeout with short deadline |\n| Two different Store interfaces | Clearly separate mock types; document which interface each mock implements |\n| `rollbackCR` has its own context timeout | Test with mock context that can be cancelled |\n| Random string generation (`RandString`) | Test length and charset, not specific values |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/client-go/clientset/versioned/clientset.go\">\nERROR [25:18] could not import github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1 (no required module provides package \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\")\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/router/main.go\">\nERROR [58:67] server.GetRouter undefined (type *router.Server has no field or method GetRouter)\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T